Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Server Engineer II* with *Leggett & Platt Inc.*. I bring over three years of professional experience building and operating cloud infrastructure, production backend systems, and DevOps pipelines, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade cloud infrastructure and operational systems that directly reflect the server and cloud administration depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with AWS CloudFormation (Infrastructure as Code) for cloud infrastructure deployments, integrating OpenTelemetry-based monitoring and alerting to enforce security best practices and compliance gates — flagging configuration drift, patch failures, and safety violations before every production release. I also engineered a FastMCP server exposing 160+ backend actions with built-in monitoring, logging, and structured operational runbooks, enforcing tenant-aware identity and access management and security policies across multi-tenant enterprise customers with audit-grade observability. To support these production workloads, I deployed and managed infrastructure on AWS (EC2, RDS, S3) serving 10,000+ users, implementing role-based access control and CloudWatch alerting to maintain availability and security compliance. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to backbone infrastructure relied on daily by enterprise clients. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot supporting cloud migration and disaster recovery across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — maintaining business continuity across hybrid cloud environments. I also orchestrated backup and disaster recovery workflows with AWS Step Functions, implementing automated retry logic and error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions, and optimized server performance with PostgreSQL to support lifecycle management and capacity planning. These roles have prepared me to manage, monitor, and maintain enterprise server and cloud infrastructure at scale, and to contribute meaningfully to Leggett & Platt's Global Server Operations team.

My academic work at Pace University reinforced the operational rigor I bring to infrastructure roles. Through research in distributed systems and cloud-native tooling, I developed disciplined approaches to high-availability design, fault-tolerant orchestration, and automated recovery — skills directly applicable to provisioning, patching, and maintaining cloud resources at an enterprise scale. I value meticulous documentation and runbook-driven operations, and I approach every infrastructure decision with the mindset of an owner — ensuring that what I build is secure, observable, and maintainable by the team long after I'm done.

I have always been passionate about *Put People First* and *Do the Right Thing* — the belief that technology exists to support the people who depend on it — and I envision myself contributing my talent to the mission of ensuring people across the world have a little more comfort in their lives through reliable, resilient infrastructure. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

